# Sitecore Marketer MCP ‚Äî Item Storage Locations

When working with the Sitecore Marketer MCP (Model Context Protocol) to create, manage, or reference items in Sitecore, always follow the documented content tree structure below. The Marketer MCP connects AI agents to Sitecore via the Agent API and each tool maps to an endpoint that performs actions in the platform. Items must be stored in their correct locations to ensure proper functionality, publishing, serialization, and workflow compliance.

## Quick Start: XM Cloud Component Development

The most common workflow when building headless applications with XM Cloud:

1. **Create Templates** ‚Üí Define data structure for your component
2. **Create Rendering** ‚Üí Link Sitecore item to React component
3. **Create Datasource Folder** ‚Üí Organize content items
4. **Create Datasource Items** ‚Üí Add actual content
5. **Register Component** ‚Üí Add to component-map.ts
6. **Add to Page** ‚Üí Use Pages editor to add component
   - **List components:** If the component has parent/child datasources, also add `_HorizonDatasourceGrouping` as a base template to the parent template so children appear in the Pages Content tab (see [Children in XM Cloud Pages Content Tab](#children-in-xm-cloud-pages-content-tab)).

See detailed sections below for each step.

---

## Marketer MCP Tools Overview

The Marketer MCP exposes tools grouped by use case. Each tool corresponds to an Agent API endpoint. When creating items through these tools, the items land in specific content tree locations depending on their type.

