## XM Cloud Headless Components

### Component Templates (created via `create_content_item`)

Component templates define the data structure for headless components.

**Location:** `/sitecore/templates/Project/<site-collection>/`

**Template Folder Structure:**

Templates must NOT be created loose under the site-collection root. They must be organized into category subfolders that group related templates. Use Template Folder items (Template ID: `0437fee2-44c9-46a6-abe9-28858d9fee8c`) to create the folder hierarchy.

```
/sitecore/templates/Project/<site-collection>/
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Components/                          ‚Üê Component templates (most common)
  ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Banners/
  ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Hero (Template)
  ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ HeroBanner (Template)
  ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Cards/
  ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ArticleCards (Template)
  ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ArticleCard (Template)
  ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Navigation/
  ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Header (Template)
  ‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Footer (Template)
  ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Forms/
  ‚îÇ       ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ContactForm (Template)
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Folders/                             ‚Üê Folder templates for datasource organization
  ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Hero Folder (Template)
  ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Article Cards Folder (Template)
  ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Navigation Folder (Template)
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Presentation/                        ‚Üê Page-level and layout templates
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Site/                                ‚Üê Site configuration templates
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Sites/                               ‚Üê Multi-site templates
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Taxonomy/                            ‚Üê Classification and tagging templates
```

**Key rules for template folder organization:**
- Always create a category folder before creating templates ‚Äî never put templates directly under the site-collection root
- `Components/` is the main folder for all component data templates, further subdivided by component category (Banners, Cards, Navigation, Forms, etc.)
- `Folders/` stores the folder templates used for datasource organization (e.g., "Hero Folder", "Article Cards Folder")
- Group related parent and child templates in the same subfolder (e.g., `ArticleCards` and `ArticleCard` both go under `Components/Cards/`)
- Folder names use PascalCase or descriptive names matching the component group
- When in doubt about which subfolder to use, check the existing structure first with `get_content_item_by_path` before creating new folders

**Creation Workflow ‚Äî Folders first, then templates:**

```
1. Check if category folder exists:
   get_content_item_by_path(path="/sitecore/templates/Project/mysite/Components/Cards")

2. If not, create the category folder:
   create_content_item(name="Cards", templateId="0437fee2-44c9-46a6-abe9-28858d9fee8c", parentId="<components-folder-id>")

3. Create template inside the folder:
   create_content_item(name="ArticleCard", templateId="ab86861a-6030-46c5-b394-e8f99e8b87db", parentId="<cards-folder-id>")

4. Create section and fields as children of the template (see below)
```

**Template Item Structure (3-level hierarchy):**

1. **Template Item** (Template ID: `ab86861a-6030-46c5-b394-e8f99e8b87db`)
   - The parent template definition
   - Name: Your component name in PascalCase (e.g., "ArticleCard", "Hero")

2. **Template Section** (Template ID: `e269fbb5-3750-427a-9149-7aa950b49301`)
   - Child of template item
   - Name: Usually "Data"
   - Groups related fields together

3. **Template Field Items** (Template ID: `455a3e98-a627-4b40-8035-e683a0331ac7`)
   - Children of template section
   - Each field is a separate item
   - Set the `Type` field to specify field type

**Common Field Types:**

- `Single-Line Text` ‚Äî Short text values (titles, names)
- `Multi-Line Text` ‚Äî Longer text content
- `Rich Text` ‚Äî HTML formatted content
- `Image` ‚Äî Media library images
- `General Link` ‚Äî Internal/external links
- `Checkbox` ‚Äî Boolean values
- `Date` / `DateTime` ‚Äî Date/time values
- `Number` / `Integer` ‚Äî Numeric values
- `Droplink` ‚Äî Single item reference
- `Multilist` ‚Äî Multiple item references

**Setting field values via MCP (`create_content_item` / `update_content`):**

Some field types require specific formats when passed in the `fields` payload:

- **Single-Line Text / Multi-Line Text:** Plain string value.
  `"Title": "My Article Title"`

- **Rich Text:** HTML string.
  `"Description": "<p>Some <strong>rich</strong> content</p>"`

- **General Link:** Link XML format. The value must be a Sitecore link XML string:
  `"CtaLink": "<link linktype=\"external\" url=\"https://example.com\" text=\"Learn more\" target=\"_blank\" />"`
  `"CtaLink": "<link linktype=\"internal\" id=\"{ITEM-GUID}\" text=\"Read more\" />"`
  `"CtaLink": "<link linktype=\"external\" url=\"#\" text=\"Learn more about Saga\" />"`

- **Image:** Media library item path or ID.
  `"Image": "<image mediaid=\"{MEDIA-ITEM-GUID}\" />"`

- **Checkbox:** `"1"` for true, `""` for false.
  `"IsActive": "1"`

- **Date / DateTime:** ISO format string.
  `"PublishDate": "20250217T120000Z"`

**Example Template Structure:**

```
/sitecore/templates/Project/mysite/Components/Cards/
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ArticleCard (Template)
      ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Data (Template Section)
          ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Title (Template Field, Type: "Single-Line Text")
          ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Image (Template Field, Type: "Image")
          ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Link (Template Field, Type: "General Link")
          ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ BadgeText (Template Field, Type: "Single-Line Text")
```

**Creation Workflow ‚Äî Template items:**

```
1. Create template (inside the correct category folder):
   create_content_item(name="ArticleCard", templateId="ab86861a-6030-46c5-b394-e8f99e8b87db", parentId="<cards-folder-id>")

2. Create section:
   create_content_item(name="Data", templateId="e269fbb5-3750-427a-9149-7aa950b49301", parentId="<template-id>")

3. Create fields:
   create_content_item(name="Title", templateId="455a3e98-a627-4b40-8035-e683a0331ac7", parentId="<section-id>", fields={"Type": "Single-Line Text"})
```

