### Props Shape: With vs Without Component GraphQL Query

The presence or absence of a `Component GraphQL Query` on the rendering item fundamentally changes the shape of the props your React component receives. Match your React component's props interface to the chosen option ‚Äî use either the GraphQL/jsonValue shape or the default PascalCase/.value shape, never a mix.

#### Summary Table

| Rendering has Component GraphQL Query | Props shape | Use in component |
|---------------------------------------|-------------|------------------|
| **Yes** (list / parent‚Äìchild) | `fields.data.datasource` (parent fields + `datasource.children.results` for child items), camelCase, `jsonValue` | GraphQL-style interfaces with `jsonValue` |
| **No** (simple / single-datasource) | `fields` with PascalCase keys, `.value` per field | `fields.Title`, `fields.Description`, etc. with `.value` |

#### With Component GraphQL Query (list / parent‚Äìchild components)

When the rendering has a `Component GraphQL Query` set, the layout service executes that query and returns data in a structured `data.datasource` shape. Children are nested **inside** the datasource object (not as a sibling).

- Datasource fields are under `fields.data.datasource`
- Field names use **camelCase** (as written in the GraphQL query)
- Each field has a `jsonValue` wrapper (e.g., `fields.data.datasource.title.jsonValue`)
- Children are at `fields.data.datasource.children.results` ‚Äî an array of items each with `id` and field objects with `jsonValue`

**Example interface ‚Äî ArticleCards:**

```typescript
interface ArticleCardChild {
  id: string;
  title?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
  image?: { jsonValue?: ImageField };
  link?: { jsonValue?: LinkField };
  badgeText?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
}

interface ArticleCardsFields {
  data?: {
    datasource?: {
      title?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
      children?: {
        results?: ArticleCardChild[];
      };
    };
  };
}
```

**Usage in JSX:**

```typescript
const datasource = fields?.data?.datasource;
const title = datasource?.title?.jsonValue;
const articles = datasource?.children?.results || [];
// <Text field={title} />
// articles.map(a => <Text field={a.title?.jsonValue} />)
```

**Example interface ‚Äî TrustSection (children inside datasource):**

```typescript
interface TrustPointChild {
  id: string;
  icon?: { jsonValue?: ImageField };
  heading?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
  description?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
}

interface TrustSectionFields {
  data?: {
    datasource?: {
      title?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
      subtitle?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
      children?: {
        results?: TrustPointChild[];
      };
    };
  };
}
```

**Usage in JSX:**

```typescript
const datasource = fields?.data?.datasource;
const points = datasource?.children?.results || [];
// points.map(p => <Text field={p.heading?.jsonValue} />)
```

#### Without Component GraphQL Query (simple / single-datasource components)

When the rendering has NO `Component GraphQL Query` (field is empty), the layout service uses default JSS shaping:

- Fields are on `fields` directly at the top level ‚Äî there is no `data.datasource` wrapper
- Field names use **PascalCase**, matching the Sitecore template field names exactly (e.g., `Title`, `Description`, `BackgroundImage`, `CtaLink`)
- Each field has a `value` property only ‚Äî there is no `jsonValue`

**Example interface:**

```typescript
interface HeroFields {
  Title?: { value?: string };
  Description?: { value?: string };
  BackgroundImage?: { value?: { src?: string; alt?: string } };
  CtaLink?: { value?: { href?: string; text?: string } };
}
```

**Usage in JSX:**

```typescript
// <Text field={fields.Title} />
// <Image field={fields.BackgroundImage} />
// <Link field={fields.CtaLink} />
```

**Example default layout payload (no GraphQL query):**

```json
{
  "fields": {
    "Title": { "value": "GET YOUR MONEY MOVING WITH SAGA" },
    "Description": { "value": "Designed for people over 50..." },
    "BackgroundImage": { "value": {} },
    "CtaLink": { "value": { "href": "", "text": "Boost your savings" } }
  },
  "params": { "styles": "" },
  "rendering": { "componentName": "hero", "dataSource": "..." },
  "page": { "..." : "..." }
}
```

