### Datasource Folder Organization

To use query-based datasource locations, you need folder templates and folder instances.

**1. Create Folder Template:**
- Location: `/sitecore/templates/Project/<site-collection>/Folders/`
- Base template: Standard Template or Folder Template
- Name: `<Component> Folder` (e.g., "Hero Folder", "Article Cards Folder")
- Set Insert Options to allow your component templates as children
- **For list components (parent + child datasource):** Also add `_HorizonDatasourceGrouping` as a base template to the **parent component template** (not the folder template) so child items appear in the Pages Content tab. See [Children in XM Cloud Pages Content Tab](#children-in-xm-cloud-pages-content-tab) below for details.

**2. Create Folder Instance:**
- Location: `/sitecore/content/<site>/<site>/Data/`
- Use your folder template
- Name: Plural or descriptive (e.g., "Heroes", "ArticleCards")

**3. Create Datasource Items:**
- Location: Inside the folder instance
- Use your component template
- These become selectable in the datasource picker

**Example Structure:**

```
/sitecore/content/mysite/mysite/Data/
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ArticleCards (using "Article Cards Folder" template)
      ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Article Cards Default (using "ArticleCards" template)
      ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Julia Bradbury Packing (using "ArticleCard" child template)
      ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Perfect Pancakes (using "ArticleCard" child template)
      ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Scammers Article (using "ArticleCard" child template)
      ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Homepage Articles (using "ArticleCards" template)
```

**Why This Pattern:**
- Better organization of datasources by type
- Reusable datasources across multiple pages
- Clearer content structure for authors
- Enables datasource picker filtering via query

