### Component Registration Workflow

After creating all Sitecore items, the React component must be registered in the Next.js application.

**1. Component File:**
- Path: `src/components/<category>/<component-name>.tsx`
- Use kebab-case for filename: `article-cards.tsx`, `hero.tsx`
- Must export named variants: `export const Default`, `export const ImageBottom`, etc.
- Use `ComponentProps` from `@/lib/component-props`
- Import ONLY from `@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs` (never from `/config-cli` or `/tools`)

**2. Register in Component Map:**
- File: `.sitecore/component-map.ts`
- Import: `import * as articlecards from 'src/components/ui/article-cards';`
- Map entry: `['article-cards', { ...articlecards, componentType: 'client' }]`
- The key MUST match the rendering's `componentName` field exactly

**Example Registration:**

```typescript
// .sitecore/component-map.ts
import * as articlecards from 'src/components/ui/article-cards';
import * as hero from 'src/components/ui/hero';

export const componentMap = new Map<string, NextjsContentSdkComponent>([
  ['article-cards', { ...articlecards, componentType: 'client' }],
  ['hero', { ...hero }],
]);
```

**3. Component Code Pattern:**

Choose the pattern that matches your rendering configuration. If the rendering has a `Component GraphQL Query`, use the GraphQL/jsonValue pattern. If the field is empty, use the default JSS pattern.

**Pattern A: With Component GraphQL Query (list / parent‚Äìchild, e.g., ArticleCards)**

```typescript
'use client';

import type React from 'react';
import { Text, Image, Link } from '@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs';
import { Field, ImageField, LinkField } from '@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs';
import { ComponentProps } from '@/lib/component-props';

// GraphQL shape: fields.data.datasource (with children inside), camelCase, jsonValue
interface ArticleCardChild {
  id: string;
  title?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
  image?: { jsonValue?: ImageField };
  link?: { jsonValue?: LinkField };
  badgeText?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
}

interface ArticleCardsFields {
  data?: {
    datasource?: {
      title?: { jsonValue?: Field<string> };
      children?: {
        results?: ArticleCardChild[];
      };
    };
  };
}

interface ArticleCardsProps extends ComponentProps {
  params: { [key: string]: any };
  fields: ArticleCardsFields;
}

export const Default: React.FC<ArticleCardsProps> = (props) => {
  const { fields, page } = props;
  const isEditing = page.mode.isEditing;
  const datasource = fields?.data?.datasource;
  const title = datasource?.title?.jsonValue;
  const articles = datasource?.children?.results || [];

  return (
    <section>
      {title && <Text field={title} />}
      {articles.map((article) => (
        <div key={article.id}>
          <Image field={article.image?.jsonValue} />
          <Text field={article.title?.jsonValue} />
          <Link field={article.link?.jsonValue} />
        </div>
      ))}
    </section>
  );
};
```

**Pattern B: Without Component GraphQL Query (simple / single-datasource, e.g., Hero)**

```typescript
'use client';

import type React from 'react';
import { Text, Image, Link } from '@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs';
import { ComponentProps } from '@/lib/component-props';

// Default JSS shape: fields at top level, PascalCase, .value
interface HeroFields {
  Title?: { value?: string };
  Description?: { value?: string };
  BackgroundImage?: { value?: { src?: string; alt?: string } };
  CtaLink?: { value?: { href?: string; text?: string } };
}

interface HeroProps extends ComponentProps {
  params: { [key: string]: any };
  fields: HeroFields;
}

export const Default: React.FC<HeroProps> = (props) => {
  const { fields, page } = props;
  const isEditing = page.mode.isEditing;

  return (
    <section>
      <Text field={fields.Title} />
      <Text field={fields.Description} />
      <Image field={fields.BackgroundImage} />
      <Link field={fields.CtaLink} />
    </section>
  );
};
```

**4. Verification Checklist:**
- Component appears in Pages editor component toolbar
- Datasource picker shows available items when adding to page
- Fields are editable inline in editing mode
- Component renders correctly on the published site
- For list components: children appear in the Content tab with sort/add/delete controls (requires `_HorizonDatasourceGrouping` on parent template)

