## Complete Example: Creating an ArticleCards Component

### Step 1: Create Templates via MCP

**Parent template (ArticleCards):**

```
create_content_item(
  name="ArticleCards",
  templateId="ab86861a-6030-46c5-b394-e8f99e8b87db",
  parentId="<project-templates-folder-id>"
)
# Create "Data" section, then "Title" field (Single-Line Text)
# Add _HorizonDatasourceGrouping as base template (see Step 1b)
```

**Child template (ArticleCard):**

```
create_content_item(
  name="ArticleCard",
  templateId="ab86861a-6030-46c5-b394-e8f99e8b87db",
  parentId="<project-templates-folder-id>"
)
# Create "Data" section, then fields: Image, Title, Link, BadgeText
```

**Step 1b: Enable child management in Pages Content tab:**

```
# Add _HorizonDatasourceGrouping as a base template to the PARENT template (ArticleCards)
update_content(
  itemId="<articlecards-template-id>",
  siteName="mysite",
  fields={
    "__Base template": "<existing-base-template-ids>|{D0F6BE14-2A2D-4C56-ACB5-80CAA573B8E2}"
  }
)

# Set Insert Options on ArticleCards Standard Values to allow ArticleCard as a child
# This enables the "Add" button in the Pages Content tab
```

### Step 2: Create Folder Template

```
create_content_item(
  name="Article Cards Folder",
  templateId="ab86861a-6030-46c5-b394-e8f99e8b87db",
  parentId="<project-templates-folder-id>"
)
# Set insert options to allow ArticleCards template
```

### Step 3: Create Rendering

```
# Renderings mirror the template folder structure
create_content_item(
  name="ArticleCards",
  templateId="04646a89-996f-4ee7-878a-ffdbf1f0ef0d",
  parentId="<cards-renderings-folder-id>"
)

update_content(
  itemId="<rendering-id>",
  siteName="mysite",
  fields={
    "componentName": "article-cards",
    "Datasource Template": "/sitecore/templates/Project/mysite/Components/Cards/ArticleCards",
    "Datasource Location": "query:$site/*[@@name='Data']/*[@@templatename='Article Cards Folder']|query:$sharedSites/*[@@name='Data']/*[@@templatename='Article Cards Folder']",
    "AddFieldEditorButton": "1",
    "ComponentQuery": "query ArticleCards($datasource: String!, $language: String!) { datasource: item(path: $datasource, language: $language) { ... on ArticleCards { title { jsonValue } } children { results { ... on ArticleCard { id title { jsonValue } image { jsonValue } link { jsonValue } badgeText { jsonValue } } } } } }"
  }
)
```

### Step 4: Create Datasource Structure

```
# Create folder instance in Data
create_content_item(
  name="ArticleCards",
  templateId="<article-cards-folder-template-id>",
  parentId="<site-data-folder-id>"
)

# Create parent datasource
create_content_item(
  name="Article Cards Default",
  templateId="<articlecards-template-id>",
  parentId="<articlecards-folder-id>",
  fields={"Title": "Latest Articles"}
)

# Create child items
create_content_item(
  name="Julia Bradbury Article",
  templateId="<articlecard-template-id>",
  parentId="<parent-datasource-id>",
  fields={"Title": "Julia Bradbury: My worst packing disaster", "BadgeText": "ARTICLE"}
)
```

### Step 5: Create React Component

File: `src/components/ui/article-cards.tsx`

### Step 6: Register in Component Map

File: `.sitecore/component-map.ts`

```typescript
import * as articlecards from 'src/components/ui/article-cards';

export const componentMap = new Map([
  ['article-cards', { ...articlecards, componentType: 'client' }],
]);
```

### Step 7: Add to Page

1. Open the page in Sitecore Pages editor
2. Click "Add Component" on a placeholder
3. Find "ArticleCards" in the component list
4. Select datasource from the picker
5. Component appears on page with editable fields
6. In the Content tab, child items (ArticleCard) appear with sort, add, rename, and delete controls (enabled by `_HorizonDatasourceGrouping`)

