## Common Issues and Solutions

### Template Creation

**`list_available_insertoptions` fails on template folders:**
This is expected ‚Äî the tool requires a site root ancestor. Not applicable to template folders.

**Fields not appearing in datasource picker:**
Ensure the template has the proper 3-level structure: Template ‚Üí Section ‚Üí Fields.

### Rendering Configuration

**"No datasource template found for component" when adding to page:**
- Verify `Datasource Template` contains the full path (not a GUID)
- Path must start with `/sitecore/templates/...`
- Confirm the template actually exists at that path

**Component not appearing in Pages editor toolbar:**
- Verify `componentName` is set and matches the component-map key (kebab-case)
- Confirm component is registered in `.sitecore/component-map.ts`
- Rendering template must be "JSON Rendering" (not "Controller Rendering")

**Datasource picker is empty:**
- Verify the `Datasource Location` query is correct
- Folder template name in query must match the actual folder template exactly
- Folder instance must exist in the Data folder
- Folder must contain datasource items as children

**Component renders parent data but children are missing:**
- The `ComponentQuery` field on the rendering is either empty or missing the `children { results { ... } }` block
- Verify the template names in `... on <TemplateName>` fragments match the actual Sitecore template names (PascalCase)
- Verify all needed fields are listed inside the fragment with `{ jsonValue }`
- Check that field names in the query use camelCase (e.g., `badgeText` not `BadgeText`)
- For list components, you must set the query and use `fields.data.datasource.children.results` in the component

**Component expects `fields.data.children.results` but array is empty:**
- Children are nested **inside** the datasource object, not as a sibling. Use `fields.data.datasource.children.results`, not `fields.data.children.results`.

**Component expects `fields.data.datasource` but receives `fields.Title` (or vice versa):**
- This is a props shape mismatch between the rendering configuration and the component code
- If the rendering has NO `Component GraphQL Query`: the component receives the default JSS shape ‚Äî fields at top level with PascalCase keys and `.value` (e.g., `fields.Title.value`, `fields.Description.value`). Use the default pattern in the component.
- If the rendering HAS a `Component GraphQL Query`: the component receives the GraphQL shape ‚Äî `fields.data.datasource` with camelCase keys and `.jsonValue`. Use the GraphQL pattern in the component.
- Fix: either add a GraphQL query to the rendering and update the component to the `data.datasource`/`jsonValue` shape, or remove the query and update the component to the PascalCase/`.value` shape. Never mix both.

**Children not appearing in Pages Content tab:**
- Add `_HorizonDatasourceGrouping` (`{D0F6BE14-2A2D-4C56-ACB5-80CAA573B8E2}`) as a base template to the **parent** datasource template (e.g., ArticleCards, CategoryDirectory) ‚Äî not the child template and not the folder template.
- Set Insert Options on the parent template's **Standard Values** to allow the child template. Without Insert Options, the "Add" button in the Content tab won't know which templates to offer.
- Verify the `_HorizonDatasourceGrouping` template exists at `/sitecore/templates/Foundation/Experience Accelerator/Horizon/_HorizonDatasourceGrouping`. If it doesn't exist, your XM Cloud environment may not have SXA installed or the path may differ.
- Ensure child items actually exist under the parent datasource item in the content tree. The Content tab reflects the real item hierarchy.

### Component Registration

**Component renders but fields are not editable:**
- Use Sitecore field components (`Text`, `Image`, `Link`)
- Access fields via the `jsonValue` property
- Handle `isPageEditing` prop correctly

**Component name mismatch errors:**
Verify the entire naming chain matches:
- File: `article-cards.tsx`
- Import: `import * as articlecards`
- Map key: `['article-cards', {...}]`
- Rendering: `componentName: "article-cards"`

**TypeScript errors in component:**
- Import only from `@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs` (main package)
- Never import from `/config-cli`, `/tools`, or `/client` subpaths
- Props interface must extend `ComponentProps`
- Use optional chaining (`?.`) for all nested field access

### Build and Deployment

**Component not appearing after registration:**
- Restart the Next.js dev server after changes to `component-map.ts`
- Clear the `.next` cache folder and rebuild if needed

